Step 1: Install WSL(if not present)
Open PowerShell as Administrator and run:
wsl --install
or  if installed just wsl

step 2: Update Ubuntu
Paste: sudo apt update
Enter your Ubuntu password.

Step 3: Install Ansible
Paste: sudo apt install ansible -y

Step 4: Verify Ansible
Paste: ansible --version

step 5:Create Project Folder
mkdir ansible_localhost
cd ansible_localhost

Step 6: Create Inventory File
nano inventory
[local]
localhost ansible_connection=local

Save;
Ctrl + O
Enter
Ctrl + X

Step 7: Test Inventory
ansible all -i inventory -m ping

Output:
localhost | SUCCESS
ping : pong

Step 8: Create Playbook
nano ansible.yml
---
- name: Install and run nginx on localhost
  hosts: local
  become: yes

  tasks:

    - name: Install nginx
      apt:
        name: nginx
        state: present
        update_cache: yes

    - name: Start nginx
      service:
        name: nginx
        state: started
        enabled: yes

Step 9: Run Playbook
sudo ansible-playbook -i inventory ansible.yml -K

Step 10: Open Apache Page
curl http://localhost
